etymologies: mid 19th century: from Greek eukritos ‘easily discerned’, from eu- ‘well’ + kritos ‘separated’ (from krinein ‘to separate’)

definitions: a highly basic form of gabbro containing anorthite or bytownite with augite.
shortDefinitions: highly basic form of gabbro containing anorthite or bytownite with augite

definitions: a stony meteorite which contains no chondrules and consists mainly of anorthite and augite.
shortDefinitions: stony meteorite which contains no chondrules and consists mainly of anorthite and augite
